19/10/2019, 9:48 am - Abhishek Jain Svvv: Synchrocyclotron
A synchrocyclotron is a modified cyclotron, in which the frequency of the RF oscillator is varied to compensate for decreased frequency of accelerating proton with increase in mass.

The frequency of R F Oscillator is decreased in steps of 10-20 Cycles/sec by rotating the movable vanes of the capacitor, thus the resonance condition is established between particle and RF frequency, and the particle energy can be further increased by increasing the radius of dees.

The acceleration of particles takes place as they enter or leave Dee at the outer edge, the ion beam can be removed with the help of deflector. It was possible to produce 200MeV deuterons and 400MeV Î±-particle with the first synchrocyclotron.

Difference between Cyclotron and Synchrocyclotron

1. In Synchrocyclotron  frequency of RF oscillator is varied whereas it was kept constant in Cyclotron.

2. In Synchrocyclotron single dee can be used instead of two, the other end of the oscillating voltage supply being connected to earth.

Advantage of the synchrocyclotron

1. There is no need to restrict the number of revolutions executed by the ion before its exit

2. The potential difference supplied between the dees can be kept smaller.
ï¿¼

AÂ byteÂ is 8Â bitsâ€¦so just likeÂ you canÂ make a number like 1635 from four decimal digits -Â you canÂ make a number like 10110110 out of eight binary digits. 2 Write and prove Demorgan's 1st & 2nd theorem with statements?

DeMorganâ€™s First Theorem

DeMorganâ€™s First theorem proves that when two (or more) input variables areÂ ANDâ€™edÂ and negated, they are equivalent to theÂ ORÂ of the complements of the individual variables. Thus the equivalent of theÂ NANDÂ function and is a negative-OR function proving thatÂ A.BÂ =Â A+B


DeMorganâ€™s Second theorem proves that when two (or more) input variables areÂ ORâ€™edÂ and negated, they are equivalent to theÂ ANDÂ of the complements of the individual variables. Thus the equivalent of theÂ NORÂ function and is a negative-AND function proving thatÂ A+BÂ =Â A.BÂ

3. Write the applications of various logic gates?

Printer I.C., Power management I.C., Disk Drive read-write I.C., Inside thumb drive electronics, Automotive (GM) courtesy light, F14 electronics to control and make early warning counter measure decisions. Agile RADAR aircraft antenna system, control for an electronic automatic RF attenuator. Used in nearly every integrated circuit that I have ever designed.

4. What do you mean by positive logic system and negative logic system?

When a circuit requiresÂ logicÂ 1 to operate, engineers may refer to this condition asÂ positive logic. Thus, the moreÂ positiveÂ voltage causes the action to take place. On the other hand, if a circuit requires aÂ logicÂ 0 to cause action, this type circuit is referred to asÂ negative logic

5. What are the uses of Boolean algebra?
Two things about Boolean algebra make it a very important form of mathematics for practical applications. First, statements expressed in everyday language (such as "I will be home today") can be converted into mathematical expressions, such as letters and numbers. Second, those symbols generally have only one of two values. The statements above (P and Q), for example, are either true or false. That means they can be expressed in a binary system: true or false; yes or no; 0 or 1.

Binary mathematics is the number system most often used with computers. Computer systems consist of magnetic cores that can be switched on or switched off. The numbers 0 and 1 are used to represent the two possible states of a magnetic core. Boolean statements can be represented, then, by the numbers 0 and 1 and also by electrical systems that are either on or off. As a result, when engineers design circuitry for personal computers, pocket calculators, compact disc players, cellular telephones, and a host of other electronic products, they apply the principles of Boolean

03/03/2020, 8:41 pm - Kushagra Ahire Svvv: #include<stdio.h>
#include<process.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
 
#define MAX 5	//Maximum number of elements that can be stored
 
int top=-1,stack[MAX];
void push();
void pop();
void display();
 
void main()
{
	int ch;
	
	while(1)	//infinite loop, will end when choice will be 4
	{
		printf("\n*** Stack Menu ***");
		printf("\n\n1.Push\n2.Pop\n3.Display\n4.Exit");
		printf("\n\nEnter your choice(1-4):");
		scanf("%d",&ch);
		
		switch(ch)
		{
			case 1: push();
					break;
			case 2: pop();
					break;
			case 3: display();
					break;
			case 4: exit(0);
			
			default: printf("\nWrong Choice!!");
		}
	}
}
 
void push()
{
	int val;
	
	if(top==MAX-1)
	{
		printf("\nStack is full!!");
	}
	else
	{
		printf("\nEnter element to push:");
		scanf("%d",&val);
		top=top+1;
		stack[top]=val;
	}
}
 
void pop()
{
	if(top==-1)
	{
		printf("\nStack is empty!!");
	}
	else
	{
		printf("\nDeleted element is %d",stack[top]);
		top=top-1;
	}
}
 
void display()
{
	int i;
	
	if(top==-1)
	{
		printf("\nStack is empty!!");
	}
	else
	{
		printf("\nStack is...\n");
		for(i=top;i>=0;--i)
			printf("%d\n",stack[i]);
	}
}

13/04/2020, 10:56 am - Abhishek Jain Svvv: You have following code..
You have to add only Name in Enter Msg..

//I n h e r i t a n c e
//Single Inheritance OneBaseClass <- OneDerivedClass (B1 <-D1)
//B1[(pvt DM SName)and (pub MF ReadSName() WriteSName())]
//{L1}OtherAct(B2) [Student(B1)<- {L2}Enroll(D1)<-{L3}YrSem(D2)<-{L4}Th_Marks, Pr_Marks]<-{L5}Result
//SingleInh + MultilevelInh + HierarchicalInh + MultipleInh + virtual
//Hybrid Inh
//Last Program
//I n h e r i t a n c e
//Single Inheritance OneBaseClass <- OneDerivedClass (B1 <-D1)
//B1[(pvt DM SName)and (pub MF ReadSName() WriteSName())]
//Base1 Class
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
class Student
{
protected: string SName;
public:
void ReadSName(){cout<<"Enter Student Name:";cin>>SName;}
void WriteSName(){cout<<"My name is "<<SName;}
string ReturnSName(){ return SName;}
};
//Derived1 Class
//D1[(Enrollment)and (ReadEn WriteEn)]
class Enroll: public Student
{
protected: string Enrollment;
public:
void ReadEnroll()
{cout<<"\nEnter Enrollment of "<<SName;cin>>Enrollment;}
void WriteEnroll()
{cout<<"My Enrollment No is "<<Enrollment;}
void FullInformation()
{
cout<<"\nMy name is "<<SName<<endl;
cout<<"and my Enrollment no is "<<Enrollment<<endl;
}
};
//Multilevel B1 <- D1 <-D2
//D2 [(Year/Sem) and (ReadYrSem() WriteYrSem())]
class YrSem:public Enroll
{
protected: int Yr, Sem;
public:
void ReadYrSem()
{cout<<"Enter Year and Sem:"; cin>>Yr>>Sem;}
void WriteYrSem()
{cout<<"\nI am studing in Year "<<Yr;
cout<<"and Sem "<<Sem;}
void FullInformation()
{
cout<<"\nMy name is "<<SName<<endl;
cout<<"and my Enrollment no is "<<Enrollment<<endl;
cout<<"\nI am studing in Year "<<Yr;
cout<<"and Sem "<<Sem;
}
};
//HierarchicalInh LD31 + RD32
//LD31
class Th_Marks : public YrSem
{
private:
int M2, DLCD, DSA, CSO, OOP, TotTh;
public:
void ReadThMarks()
{
cout<<"\nEnter Th Marks of M2, DLCD, DSA, CSO, OOP :";
cin>>M2>>DLCD>>DSA>>CSO>>OOP;
}
void WriteThMarks()
{
cout<<"\nMarks of M2, DLCD, DSA, CSO, OOP :\n";
cout<<M2<<","<<DLCD<<","<<DSA<<","<<CSO<<","<<OOP;
}
int TotalTh_Marks(){ TotTh = M2 + DLCD+ DSA+ CSO + OOP; return TotTh;}
};
//RD32
class Pr_Marks : public YrSem
{
private:
int DLCD, DSA, OOP, CS, TotPr;
public:
void ReadPrMarks()
{
cout<<"\nEnter Pr Marks of DLCD, DSA, OOP, CS :";
cin>>DLCD>>DSA>>OOP>>CS;
}
void WritePrMarks()
{
cout<<"\nMarks of DLCD, DSA, OOP, CS :\n";
cout<<DLCD<<","<<DSA<<","<<OOP<<","<<CS;
}
int TotalPr_Marks(){ TotPr = DLCD+ DSA+ OOP+ CS; return TotPr;}
};
//HybridInh
class OtherAct
{
int Sports, NPTEL, TotAct;
public:
void ReadOthAct()
{
cout<<"Enter Marks of Sports and NPTEL :";
cin>>Sports>>NPTEL;
}
void WriteOthAct()
{
cout<<"\nMarks of Sports , NPTEL\n";
cout<<Sports<<" , "<<NPTEL<<endl;
}
int TotalOtheAct()
{ TotAct = Sports+NPTEL;
return TotAct;}
};
//MultipleInh
//D4 {L4}
class Result : public Th_Marks, public Pr_Marks, public OtherAct
{
int FinalMarks;
public:

void FullInformation()
{
ReadOthAct();
cout<<"\nMy name is "<<Th_Marks::SName<<endl;
cout<<"and my Enrollment no is "<<Th_Marks::Enrollment<<endl;
cout<<"I am studing in Year "<<Th_Marks::Yr;
cout<<"and Sem "<<Th_Marks::Sem;
WriteThMarks();
WritePrMarks();
WriteOthAct();
MarkSheet();
}
void MarkSheet()
{ cout<<"\nmy Grade is ";
FinalMarks = (TotalTh_Marks()*60 /100) + (TotalPr_Marks()*40 /100 + (TotalOtheAct() *20 /100));
if (FinalMarks > 460) cout<<"A";
else if (FinalMarks > 400) cout<<"B";
else if (FinalMarks > 300) cout<<"C";
else if (FinalMarks > 100) cout<<"D";
else cout<<"F";
}

};
int main()
{
Result S; //[B2 P1 (B1<-D1<-D2<-LD31<-ST) |P2 (B1<-D1<-D2<-RD32<-SP)] <= D4 <=S
S.Th_Marks::ReadSName();//Base1
S.Th_Marks::ReadEnroll();//Derived1
S.Th_Marks::ReadYrSem(); //Derived2
S.ReadThMarks();//Derived31//LD31
S.ReadPrMarks();//Derived32//LD32
S.FullInformation();
return 0;

11/06/2020, 7:17 pm - Abhishek Jain Svvv: *Do you know what is suspended_coffee?*

A woman giving money at a restaurant counter in Norway and told,
*"Five coffee, two suspended".* Gave money for five coffees and carried three cups of coffee.

Another came and ordered,
*"Ten coffee, five suspended"* He paid for ten and grabbed five coffees.

And another ordered,
*"Five meals, two suspended"* He paid for five meals and took three lunch packets.
.
.
.
An old man for a while, came to the counter with shabby clothes.

*"Any suspended coffee?"* He asked.

The woman at the counter said, *"Yes," and served a cup of  hot coffee.*

As soon as another bearded man came in and asked *"Any Suspended Meals".?* The man at the counter  gave a parcel of hot rice and a bottle of water.

*Helping the unknown poor even without knowing their faces is a kind act of humanity.*

What a remarkable gesture! This good act has come to a country in Europe and is spreading throughout the world. 

Hope we too can grow to this level.

17/07/2020, 9:06 am - Abhishek Jain Svvv: Me: Hello God.
God: Hello...

Me: I'm falling apart. Can you put me back together?
God: I'd rather not.

Me: Why?
God: Because you're not a puzzle.

Me: What about all the pieces of my life that fall to the ground?
God: Leave them there for a while. They fell for a reason. Let them be there for a while and then decide if you need to get any of those pieces back.

Me: You don't understand! I'm breaking apart!
God: No, you don't understand. You're 
transcending, evolving. What you feel are growing pains. You're getting rid of the things and people in your life that are holding you back. The pieces are not falling down. The pieces are putting in place. Relax. Take a deep breath and let those things you no longer need fall down. Stop clinging to pieces that are no longer for you. Let them fall. Let them go.

Me: Once I start doing that, what will I have left?
God: Only the best pieces of you. 

Me: I'm afraid to change.
God: I keep telling you: YOU'RE NOT CHANGING! YOU'RE BECOMING!

Me: Becoming, Who?
God: Becoming who I created you to be! A person of light, love, charity, hope, courage, joy, mercy, grace and compassion. I made you for so much more than those shallow pieces you decided to adorn yourself with and that you cling to with so much greed and fear. Let those things fall off you. I love you! Don't change! Become! Don't change! Become! Become who I want you to be, who I created. I'm gonna keep telling you this until you remember.

Me: There goes another piece.
God: Yes. Let it be like this.

Me: So... I'm not broken?
God: No, but you're breaking the darkness, like dawn. It's a new day. Become!! Become who you really are!!

04/01/2021, 10:28 am - +91 96852 12898: Dear Student,
Greetings of the Day

This is just a practice test. In this demo test you need to enter your email id, but in the actual test you will be required to have an enrollment number and password to take the test. The main examination link & password will be sent to you before commencement of the examination separately. 

For Laptop and Desktop Users (Windows Only):  
Please find the below SEB link to appear in the demo test for online End Semester Theory Examination.  This link is for windows only.


https://online.cbexams.com/RPS/svvvsebdemotest/default.aspx



Steps for demo test (For Windows Users):

Read all the instructions carefully given on the web page.
Download and Install Demo Test File.
Download and run configuration file.
Enter your e-mail Id.
Give camera permission and press the take snapshot button.
Click on the next button.
Read the instructions and start the demo test.
Attempt Part-A having 24 multiple choice questions (60 Minutes).
Attempt Part-B having 5 Descriptive type questions(3 need to be answered in 60 Minutes)
Generate PDF for each question and upload it corresponding to the respective question. 
Once the test starts (for laptop/desktop users only) you will not stop/close it until the last question gets attempted.
To stop/close the test (for laptop/desktop users only) you are required to enter an exit password which will be shown on successful completion of the test.
To enter the exit password you need to press control + q buttons.

For Mobile Users(Android Only):
Please find the below URL to appear in the demo test for online End Semester Theory Examination.

https://online.cbexams.com/svvvendsemdemotest2021/login.aspx  

Steps for demo test (For Android Users):

Click on the demo test link.
Enter your email id.
Give camera permission and press the take snapshot button.
Click on the next button.
Read the instructions and start the demo test.
Attempt Part-A having 24 multiple choice questions (60 Minutes).
Attempt Part-B having 5 Descriptive type questions(3 need to be answered in 60 Minutes)
Generate PDF for each question and upload it corresponding to the respective question.
Exit password is not required for mobile users.
Note - Demo test is compulsory for the online MST examinations.

General Instructions:
End semester theory exam will be conducted in two shifts, first from 11:00 AM to 01:00 PM and Second from 2:30 PM to 4:30 PM Institute wise. Students are required to verify their exam schedule with their respective class coordinator/ University website.
Candidates are required to connect their device (Mobile, Laptop, Desktop, etc) using examination URL before 15 min (i.e. 10:45 AM for first shift and 2:15 PM for second shift) so that in case of technical issues it can be resolved before commencement of Examination.
No candidate will be allowed to appear in the test after 30 min from commencement of examination (i.e. 11:30 AM for first shift and 3:00 PM for second shift). 
If a candidate starts the test late due to His/Her own reason, no extra time will be given to them.
While answering the question, students will NOT have the option to go back or review or modify any previously answered questions. Students will be able to go only to the next question in sequential order.   
There is no negative marking for wrong answers.
Candidates are required to use the updated Chrome browser only for taking the test.
Please find the attachments for detailed instructions and camera troubleshooting guide. 
Students are required to give camera permission at the start of the test. 
Refer camera troubleshooting guide for any camera related problems, even if problem persists students are required to change the device.

Remark: Read all the instructions carefully before appearing in examination. 

Good Luck


Thanks & Regards 
SVVV Online Examination Team

06/01/2021, 10:31 am - +91 96852 12898: For Laptop and Desktop Users (Windows Only):  
Please find the below SEB link to appear in the main test for online End Semester Theory Examination.  This link is for windows only.


https://online.cbexams.com/RPS/svvvseblivetest2020/default.aspx


Steps for main test (For Windows Users):

Read all the instructions carefully given on the web page.
Download and Install Live Test File (If you have installed SEB (Safe Exam Browser 2.4) during demo test and using the same laptop/system for Main test, it is not required to install again.)
Download and run configuration file.
Enter exam roll number and password.
Give camera permission and press the take snapshot button.
Click on the next button.
Read the instructions and start the test.
Attempt Part-A having 24 multiple choice questions (60 Minutes).
Attempt Part-B having 5 Descriptive type questions (3 need to answered in 60 Minutes)
Write the answers in the sheet.(In front of the camera)
Take a picture and generate question wise PDF.
Do not finish Part-B, Just Exit from Safe Exam Browser (press Control+q and enter exit password 321654987)
Transfer PDF to your laptop/desktop
Login again using safe exam browser
Now finish Part-B
Upload the PDF within 15 minutes
Note: All the students are required to upload answer sheets within 15 minutes after completion of the online Examination. If a student fails to upload files within 15 minutes evaluation will be done based on the first part only. no extra time will be given for uploading of files in any condition. Students required to ensure better Internet connection during examination.

For Mobile Users(Android Only):
Please find the below URL to appear in the main test for online End Semester Theory Examination.

https://online.cbexams.com/svvvesmobiletest2021/login.aspx

Click on the main test link.
Enter exam roll number and password.

Read the instructions and start the demo test.

Attempt Part-B having 5 Descriptive type questions (3 need to answered in 60 Minutes)
Write the answers in the sheet.(In front of the camera)
Generate PDF for each question and upload it corresponding to the respective question(Within 15 Mins after test).

Note: All the students are required to upload answer sheets within 15 minutes after completion of the online Examination. If a student fails to upload files within 15 minutes evaluation will be done based on the first part only. no extra time will be given for uploading of files in any condition. 07/06/2021, 6:26 pm - +91 78913 16433: Link state routing is the second family of routing protocols. While distance vector routers use a distributed algorithm to compute their routing tables, link-state routing uses link-state routers to exchange messages that allow each router to learn the entire network topology. Based on this learned topology, each router is then able to compute its routing table by using a shortest path computation.
Link State Routing has two phases:
Reliable Flooding
Initial state: Each node knows the cost of its neighbors.
Final state: Each node knows the entire graph.
Route Calculation
Each node uses Dijkstra's algorithm on the graph to calculate the optimal routes to all nodes.
The Link state routing algorithm is also known as Dijkstra's algorithm which is used to find the shortest path from one node to every other node in the network.
The Dijkstra's algorithm is an iterative, and it has the property that after kth iteration of the algorithm, the least cost paths are well known for k destination nodes.

22/06/2021, 1:26 pm - Romil Sir: Dear Student,
Greetings of the Day

Please find the link below to take a Demo test. This is just a practice test. You can take the test on either Windows or Android platform only(iOS platform is not allowed). In this demo test you need to enter your email id, but in the actual test you will be required to have an enrollment number and password to take the test. 
The link for the main examination, User Id and password will be sent to you before commencement of the examination separately. 
Note - Demo test is compulsory to appear in the main examinations .

Exam Structure:
image.png

Exam Link For Laptop and Desktop Users (Windows Users Only):  
Please find the below SEB link to appear in the demo test. This link is for windows users only.



https://online.cbexams.com/svvvsebdemotestjune2021/default.aspx 



Steps for Demo Test (For Windows Users):

1.      Click on the demo test link.

2.      Read all the instructions carefully given on the web page.

3.      Tick on the â€œI Agreeâ€ check box and press the â€œSubmitâ€ Button.

4.      Click on the â€œProceedâ€ button to download and install safe exam browser.

5.      Click on Download(Demo Test File) link given in step 3 and download the â€œSafeExamBrowserInstaller.exeâ€ file.

6.      Double click on â€œSafeExamBrowserInstaller.exeâ€ file to install safe exam browser.

7.   After installation of safe browser click on configuration file(Demo Test) link given in step 5 to download â€œSVVVConfigfileDemo2.4.sebâ€ configuration file.

8.      Run â€œSVVVConfigfileDemo2.4.sebâ€ configuration file. (It may take 30 seconds to 1 minute depending on your system speed )

9.      If you see the message â€œDo you want to quit SEB for nowâ€ then press No button.

10.  Enter your email id and select pattern for your subject.

Â·         Pattern2 is for BBA/MBA only

Â·         Pattern1 is for rest of the courses.

11.  Now press Login button.

12.  Give camera permission and take your picture by pressing the Take Snapshot button then click on the next button.

13.  After taking your picture, this time show your Admit card in front of the camera and press the Take Snapshot and then click on the next button.

14.  Verify name and photogram and click on the Continue button.

15.  Read all the instructions carefully and click on the I Agree button.

16.  Read the symbols and associated description and press on the continue button.

17.  Now press on â€œStart the Testâ€ button.

18.  Attempt Section-A and Section-B (if applicable-for pattern2 only)

19.  Write the answers in 100 words in your own hand writing.(In front of the camera)

20.  Once you complete the answer writing, press the â€œWriting Completedâ€ button.

21.  Now press â€œYes I want to Finish my testâ€ button two times to upload the answer files (pdf).

22.  Now exit the safe exam browser by pressing Ctrl+q and enter exit password 1234.

23.  Take pictures of your answers and generate question-wise PDFs.

24.  Transfer these PDFs in your laptop.

25.  Now run â€œSVVVConfigfileDemo2.4.sebâ€ configuration file to login again and start the test.

26.  On answer uploading page press the â€œBrowseâ€ button, go to file location and select the answer file.

27.  Now press the â€œUploadâ€ button to upload the file.

28.  Once you upload the files for all three questions then press the â€œComplete Testâ€ button.

29.  Test will not be completed until all files are uploaded, file uploading for each question is mandatory.

30.  Now press the â€œYes I want to complete my testâ€ button two times to finish the test.

31.  After successful completion of test a Thank you message will appear on the screen.

32.  Now exit the safe exam browser by pressing Ctrl+q and enter exit password 1234.



Exam Link For Mobile Users(Android Users Only):
Please find the below URL to appear in the Demo test. This link is for android users only.


https://online.cbexams.com/svvvmobiledemotestjune2021/login.aspx

Steps for Demo Test (For Android Users):
1.      Click on the demo test link.

2.      Enter your email id and select pattern for your subject.

Â·         Pattern2 is for BBA/MBA only

Â·         Pattern1 is for rest of the courses.

3.      Now press Login button.

4.      Give camera permission and take your picture by pressing the Take Snapshot button then click on the next button.

5.      After taking your picture, this time show your Admit card in front of the camera and press the Take Snapshot and then click on the next button.

6.      Verify name and photograph and click on the Continue button.

7.      Read all the instructions carefully and click on the I Agree button.

8.      Read the symbols and associated description and press on the continue button.

9.      Now press on â€œStart The Testâ€ button.

10.  Do not press the back button during the test.

11.  Attempt Section-A and Section-B (if applicable-for pattern2 only)

12.  Write the answers in 100 words in your own hand writing.(In front of the camera)

13.  Once you complete the answer writing, press the â€œWriting Completedâ€ button.

14.  Now press â€œYes I want to Finish my testâ€ button two times to upload the answer files (pdf).

15.  Now minimize the browser.

16.  Take pictures of your answers and generate question-wise PDFs.

17.  Open chrome browser(using demo test link) and login again.(or Maximize the browser) 

18.  Press the â€œChoose file buttonâ€, go to file location and select the file.

19.  Now press the â€œUploadâ€ button to upload the file.

20.  Once you upload the files for all three questions then press the â€œComplete Testâ€ button.

21.  Test will not be completed until all files are uploaded, file uploading for each question is mandatory.

22.  Now press the â€œYes I want to complete my testâ€ button two times to finish the test.

23.  After successful completion of test a Thank you message will appear on the screen.

24.  Exit password is not required for mobile users. Now you can close the browser.


General Instructions:
      1.    Students are required to take demo test to minimize the technical issues during main exam.

2.    Students can take demo test at any time; Demo test link is 24*7 enabled.

3.   End semester main test theory exam will be conducted in two shifts, first from 11:00 AM to 01:00 PM and Second from 2:30 PM to 4:30 PM Institute wise. Students are required to verify their exam schedule with their respective class coordinator/ University website.

4.      Once you complete the writing work and finish the test, 15 mins will be given for uploading scripts(i.e. 2:00 - 2:15 PM for first shift and 4:30 - 4:45 PM for second shift)

5.      Extra time will not be given to upload answer sheets.

6.      Candidates are required to connect their device (Mobile, Laptop, Desktop, etc) using examination URL before 15 min (i.e. 10:45 AM for first shift and 2:15 PM for second shift) so that in case of technical issues it can be resolved before commencement of Examination.

7.      No candidate will be allowed to appear in the test after 30 min from commencement of examination (i.e. 11:30 AM for first shift and 3:00 PM for second shift).

8.      If a candidate starts the test late due to His/Her own reason, no extra time will be given to them.

9.      Students are required to take test on chrome browser only. Also make sure that you have updated the chrome browser before test.

10.  In case of any problem regarding camera use camera troubleshooting guide (Attached in mail).

11.  Candidates are required to delete cookies and disable firewall/antivirus or any other unnecessary background applications (like AnyDesk Software) before taking the exam.

12.  Any kind of short break (i.e. Washroom/Drink) during exam is not allowed.

13.  You are being invigilated / proctored by a remote proctor who will be watching you all through your exam via Web-Cam.

14.  During exam proctor/invigilator contact number are being displayed on the screen. So candidate can contact on given number if they face any issue during exam.

15.  The remote proctor has the facility to send you a warning message if found of any suspicious of you doing malpractice during the course of the examination and is authorized to intervene to pause your exam if needed.

16.  Answers to Descriptive type questions must be uploaded in the same handwriting as uploaded at the time of the demo test.

17.  Your identity such as writing your name, roll number, etc., should not be disclosed anywhere on the uploaded answer scripts.

18.  There is no negative marking for wrong answers.

19.  Once test started student cannot switch to another application of the computer, because he/she cannot exit test window.

20.  Once test is submitted Thank you message is display on the screen.

21.  During the conduct of online end semester examination following activities of the students shall be termed as Unfair Means (UFM)

a.    Not following the instructions of proctoring invigilator

b.   Taking help from others in solving the questions

c.    Use of electronic gadgets (i.e. Bluetooth device, Earphone, Smart watch etc )

d.   Leaving workstation after commencement of examination

e.    Use of subject matter in any form (i.e. Printed or Soft)

f.    Switching off the camera

g.   The handwriting of Uploaded answers to Part-B questions is not matching with the document submitted at the time of the demo test

h.   Uploading of any irrelevant file as an answer script.

i.     Uploading of Image of already written notes or any other documents as an answer.

j.     Disclose of identity on answer script in any form such as writing your name, roll number, etc.

Any student found guilty of any such activity shall be considered as a UFM case and action shall be taken against such students as per the university ordinance.



Dos and Donâ€™ts

 

Doâ€™s

 

Ã¼  Place the computer so that your back is facing the wall and there are no devices placed in the background.

Ã¼  The Room where you sit should be isolated and only you need be present for complete exam duration.

Ã¼  Sit at table with computer. Keep the desk clear of objects, papers, books and any other electronic material like Mobile phones, tablets, laptops.

Ã¼  Ensure proper lighting (no back light) so that your face is clearly visible on Cam.

Ã¼  Ensure you are dressed formally

 

Donâ€™ts

Ã»  Do not take help from others.

Ã»  Do not wear any Blue-tooth devices.

Ã»  Do not leave the work station while taking the test.

Ã»  Do not play radio/TV/ Music in the background.

Ã»  Do not let anyone enter the room.

07/09/2021, 11:22 am - Manorama Mdm Svvv: Dear Sir/Mam

The Special ATKT Examinations shall be conducted from 24th September 2021 onward and the registration link shall remain open from 7th September to 18th September. The students can register themselves through E.R.P. account. The examination shall be conducted in offline mode (written mode) at University campus only.

The eligibility criteria for appearing in Special ATKT examination:

1)     Outgoing batch students (degree awarding students) having backlog in any semester.

2)     Students who are not eligible for year promotion as per examination regulation of the University.

    I)        Students who have failed to earn 60% credits of previous year.

II)         Students of III year having backlog in I year courses.

III)       Students of IV year having any backlog in II year courses.

Before appearing students must check their internal assessment marks in that particular course.

The following students need not to apply for registration in the said examination:

1)     Regular students having backlog in recently declared result need not to register themselves.

2)     Students who have been detained in all courses of a particular semester are not eligible for year promotion such students need not to register themselves in said examination.

 

 

 

 


--
Thanks & Regards,

Dr. Shishir Jain
Controller of Examinations

12/10/2021, 11:07 am - Manorama Mdm Svvv: Greetings from SVIIT

Shri Vaishnav Vidyapeeth Vishwavidyalaya, a prestigious University based in Indore (M.P.) is organizing Void Hacks(), a national level hackathon to give deserving students a platform to enhance and build something bigger than themselves.

VoidHacks() aims to provide all the technical enthusiasts a boost by providing them with the best and most comfortable assets in the form of a 36-hour hackathon which would challenge their minds to spark and enlighten their way to innovations.

Participants can build their projects on 4 themes-
 1. Web/Mobile App development
 2. FinTech
 3. Machine learning /Artificial Intelligence
 4. HealthTech

Date : 22nd-24th October 2021
Venue: Online

Prizes worth Rs. 100000 lac.


We cordially invite your institute to be part of this rendezvous. This will be a great opportunity for all the tech-savvy students out there.  
If you think you might be able to make it, please let us know, and we will follow up by letting you know the schedule.

Check out our website:
http://voidhacks.svvv.edu.in/
 

Thank you. We look forward to hearing from you.

Regards
Team Void Hacks()

08/02/2022, 1:47 pm - Kusum Tilkar Mam: Dear Students

NMIT Hacks is a National Level Hackathon conducted by the Department of Computer Science and Engineering of Nitte Meenakshi Institute of Technology, Bangalore, annually. Over the years, there has been a continuous growth in the participation of students from various reputed institutes. 

NMIT Hacks is an open Hackathon, where tech enthusiasts are given an opportunity to ideate and develop effective solutions to real-world problems within 36 hours. This year, the event is powered by Devfolio and will be conducted in a Hybrid Mode, i.e. the event is being held in offline and online mode for the convenience of the participants. The participating teams would stand a chance to win prizes worth INR 75,000 along with additional bounty. The teams will be evaluated based on the functionality of their project prototype and innovative use of technical and creative skills which will be carried out by distinguished personalities from both Industry and Academia.

We are delighted to announce that the latest edition of our Hackathon, NMIT Hacks 2022, is scheduled to be conducted between the 1st of April to 3rd of April 2022. We are honored to invite the students of your college to take part in this event and upgrade their skill set in various emerging domains of technology.

Previously, we have received active participation with over 1300 registrations and more than 200 idea submissions from all over the country. These submissions have given a unique perspective in solving several real-world problems.

Our Hackathon is extremely beginner-friendly and participants need little to no prerequisites to enter the event. Therefore, we request you to encourage your students to participate in this event. We strive to provide a platform for enthusiastic coders and developers to network and connect with industry experts and like-minded individuals. This will provide a great learning experience to help establish themselves in the competitive field of technology and entrepreneurship. 

We are looking forward to active participation from your esteemed institute.

NOTE: The mode of conduction is subject to change based on the pandemic situation and the suggestions of the registrants.

If you havenâ€™t registered already, register now!

For registrations, visit our website: https://www.nmithacks.com/

The last date for registration and idea submission is February 28, 2022.

For regular updates and information about NMIT Hacks, visit our social media handles:

Instagram- https://www.instagram.com/nmit_hacks/

Facebook- https://www.facebook.com/NMIT-Hacks-102034238319347/

Twitter- https://mobile.twitter.com/NMIT_Hacks

LinkedIn- https://www.linkedin.com/company/nmit-hacks



Thanks & Regards,

Team NMIT Hacks

15/07/2022, 6:54 pm - +91 81208 97567: Recruitment/Selection Process:   

Walkover Technologies will follow the following Selection Procedure while recruiting the candidates against the vacancies as mentioned above:

Those meeting the educational qualifications will be taken through the following assessments, with selection at each step

Step 01: Candidate Registration & Pre-recruitment briefing to candidates by Talentise Global Pvt Ltd.
Step 02: Online Assessment - 75 mins (Logical & Coding)
Step 03: L1 Technical Virtual Interview (Personal Interview)
Step 04: L2 Technical Virtual Interview (Personal Interview)
Step 05: Founder/HR Round- Video Call
Step 06: Declaration of final selected candidates list
Step 07: Offer letters/letter of intent (LOI) of hiring/selecting the candidate will be issued subsequently.

Note: All the rounds are elimination rounds.
After the HR round if they get selected they have to take 6 weeks of training at Walkover University- that is 2 hours a day and have to clear an assessment test before the onboarding process.
